1
00:00:14,700 --> 00:00:15,800
Try it.

2
00:00:15,867 --> 00:00:17,000
Is this safe to drink?

3
00:00:17,067 --> 00:00:18,300
It's clean.

4
00:00:18,367 --> 00:00:19,500
It's rainwater.

5
00:00:19,567 --> 00:00:22,267
It's not like the acid rain
we get in the city.

6
00:00:22,333 --> 00:00:23,233
Where did you learn all this?

7
00:00:23,300 --> 00:00:24,467
From my coach.

8
00:00:24,533 --> 00:00:26,133
Miss Vinluan.

9
00:00:26,200 --> 00:00:27,167
Help!

10
00:00:32,633 --> 00:00:34,100
Yen, let's follow the sound.

11
00:00:34,200 --> 00:00:38,133
The plane where my daughter
is on board crashed.

12
00:00:38,200 --> 00:00:42,100
Maybe you can expedite
my release papers?

13
00:00:42,167 --> 00:00:44,500
Did you know that Amanda
is getting released from jail?

14
00:00:44,567 --> 00:00:46,200
The court approved her petition.

15
00:00:46,267 --> 00:00:47,833
I want you to do something.

16
00:00:47,900 --> 00:00:50,433
I want to take revenge
before she gets freed.

17
00:00:51,833 --> 00:00:54,167
I'm glad to see you again,
Yenyen.

18
00:00:55,833 --> 00:00:57,800
What about Raichu?

19
00:00:57,867 --> 00:00:59,900
Did she survive too?

20
00:00:59,967 --> 00:01:01,567
I haven't found her yet.

21
00:01:01,633 --> 00:01:04,067
I'm here with Red.

22
00:01:04,133 --> 00:01:05,800
Meet Red.

23
00:01:05,867 --> 00:01:08,767
This is not going to be easy.

24
00:01:08,867 --> 00:01:12,333
You must do the first aid
I taught you, okay?

25
00:01:20,933 --> 00:01:23,867
Amanda, how did it go?

26
00:01:23,933 --> 00:01:24,933
What did the warden say?

27
00:01:25,000 --> 00:01:26,633
Are they going
to let you out sooner?

28
00:01:27,667 --> 00:01:30,833
They can't let me go
without my release order.

29
00:01:38,567 --> 00:01:42,633
Dindi, I want to look
for Eden myself.

30
00:01:42,733 --> 00:01:45,067
I want to do something
to find her.

31
00:01:47,200 --> 00:01:51,233
The days pass by without a word
about the investigation.

32
00:01:56,667 --> 00:01:57,933
I feel like...

33
00:01:59,700 --> 00:02:03,100
I feel like I'm dying
from fear and worry.

34
00:02:10,200 --> 00:02:11,867
My daughter is missing.

35
00:02:11,933 --> 00:02:14,867
And we can't do anything
but wait.

36
00:02:18,667 --> 00:02:21,600
I want to find Eden.

37
00:02:22,767 --> 00:02:24,433
Amanda, God has mercy.

38
00:02:32,167 --> 00:02:33,133
Is that her?

39
00:02:34,400 --> 00:02:35,933
Yes, that's her.

40
00:02:36,000 --> 00:02:37,833
Okay, I'll take care of it.

41
00:02:37,900 --> 00:02:40,200
Just give my family the money.

42
00:02:40,267 --> 00:02:42,533
Make sure you do
what you set out to do.

43
00:02:42,600 --> 00:02:44,667
I got it.

44
00:02:44,733 --> 00:02:46,833
Okay, keep me updated.

45
00:02:54,267 --> 00:02:55,233
Good!

46
00:02:58,767 --> 00:02:59,767
Are you sure?

47
00:03:03,500 --> 00:03:04,533
Very good.

48
00:03:07,033 --> 00:03:07,967
Rina?

49
00:03:10,667 --> 00:03:11,867
Who were you talking to?

50
00:03:13,333 --> 00:03:14,333
Was that your brother?

51
00:03:15,700 --> 00:03:16,867
He's just asking
how we're doing.

52
00:03:18,567 --> 00:03:20,000
Why? What did he need this time?

53
00:03:21,067 --> 00:03:24,767
Didn't I tell you not to talk
to him anymore?

54
00:03:24,833 --> 00:03:28,267
He brings nothing but trouble.

55
00:03:28,333 --> 00:03:30,067
Look, Victor. He's still family.

56
00:03:30,133 --> 00:03:33,333
Okay? At least he can do things
you're not capable of doing.

57
00:03:35,267 --> 00:03:37,200
What is that supposed to mean?

58
00:03:37,267 --> 00:03:38,267
You know what I mean.

59
00:03:39,933 --> 00:03:41,900
Rina, I'm warning you.

60
00:03:41,967 --> 00:03:43,633
Your brother thinks
like a criminal.

61
00:03:43,700 --> 00:03:45,600
Don't make our problems worse.

62
00:03:45,667 --> 00:03:47,733
Our son is missing.

63
00:03:47,800 --> 00:03:50,067
We have to prioritize him!

64
00:03:50,133 --> 00:03:51,267
How dare you!

65
00:03:51,333 --> 00:03:52,633
And what? You're blaming me?

66
00:03:52,700 --> 00:03:55,033
Are you telling me that
I'm not thinking of our son?

67
00:03:56,100 --> 00:03:58,100
Look, I love Red.

68
00:03:59,633 --> 00:04:02,767
I can't bear to lose him too.

69
00:04:02,833 --> 00:04:06,533
So do everything you can
to find our son!

70
00:04:06,600 --> 00:04:10,733
Do everything in your power,
Victor!

71
00:04:25,767 --> 00:04:27,933
I'm glad that we found my coach.

72
00:04:29,000 --> 00:04:30,767
I'm not too worried anymore.

73
00:04:32,433 --> 00:04:34,000
Someone is going to help us out.

74
00:04:35,833 --> 00:04:38,200
She's a good motivator.

75
00:04:38,267 --> 00:04:39,367
You're lucky to have her.

76
00:04:43,167 --> 00:04:44,400
I owe everything to her.

77
00:04:46,400 --> 00:04:51,733
I owe her all my achievements
in life.

78
00:04:53,367 --> 00:04:56,467
Not only in sports
but in my private life as well.

79
00:05:00,300 --> 00:05:04,233
Even my dream of being
with my mom again.

80
00:05:04,333 --> 00:05:07,800
I nearly gave up several times.

81
00:05:07,867 --> 00:05:10,667
But she's been reminding me
to keep fighting.

82
00:05:12,433 --> 00:05:14,267
That's why I owe her a lot.

83
00:05:15,567 --> 00:05:19,333
She always reminds me
that I can still be with my mom.

84
00:05:22,667 --> 00:05:26,033
That all my dreams in life
will come true.

85
00:05:39,667 --> 00:05:41,967
I heard they're going
to release you soon.

86
00:05:42,033 --> 00:05:43,300
That's true.

87
00:05:43,367 --> 00:05:44,567
You've been here
for a long time.

88
00:05:45,967 --> 00:05:47,067
8 years...

89
00:05:47,133 --> 00:05:50,433
for something I didn't do.

90
00:05:50,500 --> 00:05:52,767
Are you still denying
what you did?

91
00:05:55,700 --> 00:05:57,333
Do you need anything?

92
00:05:57,400 --> 00:05:59,000
Yes.

93
00:05:59,067 --> 00:06:01,600
I just want to cut your throat!

94
00:06:11,733 --> 00:06:13,733
Don't try to fight me.

95
00:06:13,800 --> 00:06:16,400
I just want to give you
a souvenir.

96
00:06:16,467 --> 00:06:20,133
So you won't forget us.

97
00:06:47,200 --> 00:06:48,300
You beast!

98
00:06:48,367 --> 00:06:50,600
If you're trying to kill me,

99
00:06:50,667 --> 00:06:53,500
you're wasting your time
because I've long been dead!

100
00:06:56,267 --> 00:07:00,933
My daughter is my only life,
but they got me locked up here!

101
00:07:01,933 --> 00:07:04,167
They separated me from her!

102
00:07:06,100 --> 00:07:09,233
They took my rights
to care for my child!

103
00:07:09,300 --> 00:07:14,800
I lost the small hope I had
of being with her again!

104
00:07:17,633 --> 00:07:21,700
I don't know
if I'll ever see her again!

105
00:07:23,233 --> 00:07:25,533
All of you are shameless!

106
00:07:27,400 --> 00:07:30,600
All I need is my daughter!

107
00:07:31,600 --> 00:07:33,400
I need my daughter!

108
00:07:33,467 --> 00:07:35,367
I want to be with her!

109
00:07:35,433 --> 00:07:38,867
I want to get out of here
to be with my daughter!

110
00:07:43,033 --> 00:07:44,300
Hey! Stop this!

111
00:07:44,367 --> 00:07:45,367
Why are you fighting?

112
00:07:46,400 --> 00:07:47,567
How dare you!

113
00:07:47,667 --> 00:07:48,867
- Give me that!
- Monsters!

114
00:07:48,933 --> 00:07:50,767
Give me that!

115
00:07:50,833 --> 00:07:52,033
Monster!

116
00:07:54,233 --> 00:07:55,700
My daughter.

117
00:07:56,833 --> 00:07:57,767
That's enough!

118
00:07:58,767 --> 00:08:00,100
You're all evil!

119
00:08:02,233 --> 00:08:03,733
My daughter!

120
00:08:03,800 --> 00:08:04,767
Stop!

121
00:08:04,833 --> 00:08:05,833
Let's go!

122
00:08:09,667 --> 00:08:10,900
Get up!

123
00:08:20,500 --> 00:08:22,100
Good job, guys.

124
00:08:22,167 --> 00:08:24,033
Keep on working together.

125
00:08:24,100 --> 00:08:28,100
Good thing that you're working
together to achieve your goals,

126
00:08:29,133 --> 00:08:31,667
especially in this situation.

127
00:08:31,733 --> 00:08:33,200
You really need
to work together.

128
00:08:35,167 --> 00:08:37,733
Your presence
makes a difference.

129
00:08:39,167 --> 00:08:41,933
I'm just here to give you
instructions.

130
00:08:42,000 --> 00:08:43,567
You guys do the hard work.

131
00:08:45,333 --> 00:08:49,567
But we have to build
our shelter for now.

132
00:08:49,633 --> 00:08:51,467
The sun is about to set.

133
00:08:52,800 --> 00:08:53,733
Go on, Red.

134
00:08:56,433 --> 00:08:57,767
Okay, Coach.

135
00:08:57,833 --> 00:08:58,800
Come on, Yen.

136
00:09:05,333 --> 00:09:06,367
- Let's go, Red.
- Go.

137
00:09:06,433 --> 00:09:07,633
Go, guys. Go.

138
00:09:17,500 --> 00:09:21,833
You came here to tell me
that you failed?

139
00:09:23,267 --> 00:09:24,233
I'm sorry, Rina.

140
00:09:25,233 --> 00:09:27,367
I didn't know
that Amanda would fight back.

141
00:09:28,433 --> 00:09:30,233
I underestimated her.

142
00:09:33,200 --> 00:09:38,967
Why didn't you get an inmate
who could get things done?

143
00:09:40,767 --> 00:09:42,267
Rina, I can try again.

144
00:09:42,333 --> 00:09:43,600
I'll find someone else to do it.

145
00:09:45,033 --> 00:09:46,067
What for?

146
00:09:47,300 --> 00:09:49,100
What for? It's too late!

147
00:09:50,533 --> 00:09:52,333
She's about to get released!

148
00:09:53,367 --> 00:09:55,100
So annoying!

149
00:09:56,133 --> 00:09:58,000
Why don't you just
get her killed?

150
00:10:03,633 --> 00:10:04,600
No.

151
00:10:05,633 --> 00:10:06,600
No.

152
00:10:07,733 --> 00:10:12,033
That will end her suffering.

153
00:10:15,800 --> 00:10:17,833
I want her to pay.

154
00:10:21,833 --> 00:10:23,067
I won't leave her alone.

155
00:10:24,200 --> 00:10:26,767
Not until she regrets

156
00:10:28,067 --> 00:10:30,567
everything she did to my family.

157
00:10:49,633 --> 00:10:51,133
- Coach.
- Coach.

158
00:10:51,200 --> 00:10:52,733
- How are you feeling?
- Are you okay?

159
00:10:55,967 --> 00:10:57,533
I'm okay.

160
00:10:57,600 --> 00:10:59,300
I'm doing fine.

161
00:10:59,367 --> 00:11:01,633
I drink all our water, though.

162
00:11:02,700 --> 00:11:05,867
It's okay, Coach. I'm glad
you're feeling better.

163
00:11:08,267 --> 00:11:09,633
It looks like it's about
to rain.

164
00:11:09,700 --> 00:11:12,267
Rain is essential.
You have to collect rainwater.

165
00:11:12,333 --> 00:11:14,800
So we can have something
to drink.

166
00:11:14,867 --> 00:11:17,867
But for now, you have
to finish building our shelter.

167
00:11:17,933 --> 00:11:21,133
You can collect the rainwater
using the tarp.

168
00:11:22,533 --> 00:11:24,000
- Go on, hurry up. Get to work.
- Okay.

169
00:11:24,067 --> 00:11:25,200
Move.

170
00:11:25,267 --> 00:11:26,200
- Let's go, Yen.
- Okay, Coach.

171
00:11:41,567 --> 00:11:42,700
Coach!

172
00:11:42,767 --> 00:11:43,967
Coach, we finished it!

173
00:11:45,333 --> 00:11:46,533
- All right!
- Good job, guys.

174
00:11:46,600 --> 00:11:47,600
Good job.

175
00:11:48,900 --> 00:11:50,567
I'll be right back.
I'll get some bamboo sticks.

176
00:11:51,833 --> 00:11:54,700
Coach, how are you feeling?

177
00:11:54,767 --> 00:11:55,833
I'm okay.

178
00:11:58,267 --> 00:11:59,833
Don't worry about me.

179
00:11:59,900 --> 00:12:01,133
I'm doing fine.

180
00:12:03,433 --> 00:12:07,700
I told you
I could get through this.

181
00:12:08,900 --> 00:12:10,933
I got this.

182
00:12:11,000 --> 00:12:14,267
I can't die here.

183
00:12:14,333 --> 00:12:15,433
Coach.

184
00:12:21,667 --> 00:12:23,533
I'm just like you, Yenyen.

185
00:12:24,767 --> 00:12:26,067
We're the same.

186
00:12:29,000 --> 00:12:31,900
I have a family to come back to.

187
00:12:33,967 --> 00:12:35,367
My daughter.

188
00:12:35,433 --> 00:12:36,967
My daughter, Yenyen.

189
00:12:37,033 --> 00:12:38,400
I have to go back to Ana.

190
00:12:42,400 --> 00:12:44,167
She'll be 18 next month.

191
00:12:47,067 --> 00:12:53,600
I want to be there
on her birthday.

192
00:12:53,700 --> 00:12:57,267
I want her to celebrate
her birthday with me.

193
00:12:59,833 --> 00:13:01,533
It's going to happen.

194
00:13:03,667 --> 00:13:04,767
You're right.

195
00:13:05,900 --> 00:13:10,367
Just like how your long-time
dream will come true.

196
00:13:13,500 --> 00:13:16,033
Your dream of reuniting
with your mom.

197
00:13:16,100 --> 00:13:17,133
Yes, Coach.

198
00:13:22,900 --> 00:13:26,067
Being your friend
is not a coincidence.

199
00:13:28,800 --> 00:13:31,067
My daughter was separated
from me for a long time.

200
00:13:33,367 --> 00:13:34,533
Long time.

201
00:13:36,900 --> 00:13:40,433
Probably that's why God
got us together.

202
00:13:42,400 --> 00:13:46,167
To help each other out.

203
00:13:48,167 --> 00:13:51,167
You helped me when I was longing
for my daughter.

204
00:13:52,700 --> 00:13:54,267
And I was there for you when
you were longing for your mom.

205
00:13:56,067 --> 00:14:00,233
Coach, I'm so grateful
to have met you.

206
00:14:04,500 --> 00:14:07,000
That's why we're going to fight.

207
00:14:08,133 --> 00:14:10,467
- Yes, Coach.
- We will never give up.

208
00:14:11,567 --> 00:14:14,167
We will get out of this island
alive.

209
00:14:15,433 --> 00:14:16,400
Yes, Coach.

210
00:14:24,500 --> 00:14:25,967
Yen! Look at this!

211
00:14:26,033 --> 00:14:26,967
Hurry!

212
00:14:28,100 --> 00:14:29,500
I'll be right back.

213
00:14:29,600 --> 00:14:31,167
- Go on. Go to him.
- I won't take long.

214
00:14:39,600 --> 00:14:42,600
- What is it?
- Look what I found!

215
00:14:42,667 --> 00:14:43,800
Bamboo!

216
00:14:46,500 --> 00:14:48,067
What is it for?

217
00:14:48,133 --> 00:14:51,200
We're going to use this
to save the rainwater.

218
00:14:51,267 --> 00:14:54,733
- Oh! You're good!
- Right?

219
00:14:54,800 --> 00:14:57,333
But it's a little small.

220
00:14:57,400 --> 00:14:59,100
We won't be able to save
a lot of water with this.

221
00:15:02,233 --> 00:15:04,467
Wait. Wait here!

222
00:15:15,000 --> 00:15:17,000
Here, balloons!

223
00:15:17,067 --> 00:15:18,067
What are we going to do

224
00:15:18,133 --> 00:15:19,633
- with that?
- To save water.

225
00:15:44,133 --> 00:15:45,033
Hurry up. Lift it up.

226
00:15:45,100 --> 00:15:46,233
All right!

227
00:15:46,300 --> 00:15:47,867
You're great!

228
00:15:47,933 --> 00:15:50,033
Okay, let's try that.

229
00:15:50,100 --> 00:15:51,833
We don't have to think about...

230
00:15:51,900 --> 00:15:52,767
There it is!

231
00:15:52,833 --> 00:15:55,467
- It's raining!
- Yes! Just on time!

232
00:15:59,033 --> 00:16:00,800
Hurry up, I'm parched!

233
00:16:00,867 --> 00:16:01,800
Me, too!
Hold this.

234
00:16:02,867 --> 00:16:04,000
Okay.

235
00:16:05,267 --> 00:16:06,233
Let's fill this.

236
00:16:08,667 --> 00:16:09,733
There you go.

237
00:16:18,300 --> 00:16:19,967
They already have
my release order.

238
00:16:20,033 --> 00:16:21,300
I can get out of jail now.

239
00:16:23,100 --> 00:16:25,000
Have you packed your stuff?

240
00:16:25,067 --> 00:16:28,367
I have your room ready.

241
00:16:28,433 --> 00:16:30,600
I'm not sure if I want
to get out of here.

242
00:16:32,167 --> 00:16:34,233
It's been days,
and we still haven't heard

243
00:16:34,300 --> 00:16:36,767
about the plane crash.

244
00:16:36,833 --> 00:16:38,933
And how Eden is doing.

245
00:16:39,000 --> 00:16:40,000
Amanda.

246
00:16:41,300 --> 00:16:44,833
She's the only reason
why I want to get out of here.

247
00:16:44,933 --> 00:16:46,800
Why I want to continue living.

248
00:16:50,200 --> 00:16:51,867
Where is she?

249
00:16:54,167 --> 00:16:56,400
Do I still have someone
to go home to?

250
00:17:08,700 --> 00:17:09,967
We have water now!

251
00:17:10,033 --> 00:17:12,633
Yes! We have a water supply now!

252
00:17:12,700 --> 00:17:13,967
- Finally!
- It's good now!

253
00:17:14,033 --> 00:17:15,600
Is it?

254
00:17:15,700 --> 00:17:16,967
Let's go!

255
00:17:17,033 --> 00:17:18,967
Let's bring this to Coach.

256
00:17:19,033 --> 00:17:19,967
Coach!

257
00:17:21,000 --> 00:17:21,967
Coach!

258
00:17:23,133 --> 00:17:25,867
Coach, we have some water now.

259
00:17:25,933 --> 00:17:26,967
- Coach.
- Coach.

260
00:17:28,433 --> 00:17:29,400
Coach.

261
00:17:31,367 --> 00:17:32,333
Coach!

262
00:17:33,767 --> 00:17:34,800
- Coach!
- Coach!

263
00:17:34,867 --> 00:17:35,867
Coach!

264
00:17:35,933 --> 00:17:36,900
Wake up!

265
00:17:41,267 --> 00:17:42,233
What?

266
00:17:44,333 --> 00:17:46,100
What?

267
00:17:46,167 --> 00:17:47,700
Coach, wake up!

268
00:17:47,800 --> 00:17:48,700
Coach!

269
00:17:48,767 --> 00:17:50,000
Coach, wake up!

270
00:17:50,067 --> 00:17:50,933
Coach!

271
00:17:51,967 --> 00:17:53,000
Coach!

272
00:17:55,200 --> 00:17:58,700
Coach! You said we'd go home
alive!

273
00:17:58,767 --> 00:18:00,000
- Yen!
- Coach!

274
00:18:00,067 --> 00:18:04,600
You said we'd all go home
together!

275
00:18:04,667 --> 00:18:05,867
- Yen!
- Coach!

276
00:18:05,933 --> 00:18:06,933
Right, Coach?

277
00:18:07,000 --> 00:18:09,000
- Coach!
- Coach!

278
00:18:09,067 --> 00:18:10,467
Coach!

279
00:18:10,533 --> 00:18:11,667
Yen!

280
00:18:11,733 --> 00:18:14,167
- Yen!
- Coach, you promised me!

281
00:18:14,233 --> 00:18:16,433
Yen! Yen, that's enough. Yen!

282
00:18:16,500 --> 00:18:17,833
Coach, you promised me!

283
00:18:17,900 --> 00:18:18,933
Yen, she's gone.

284
00:18:19,000 --> 00:18:20,100
Stop it.

285
00:18:20,167 --> 00:18:22,000
Yen, stop.

286
00:18:23,633 --> 00:18:24,800
Coach!

287
00:18:24,867 --> 00:18:29,033
Coach, you said we'd all make it
back to our family.

288
00:18:29,100 --> 00:18:30,033
Coach!

289
00:18:31,633 --> 00:18:33,133
You said...

290
00:18:33,200 --> 00:18:37,033
You said you'd be there
for your daughter's birthday.

291
00:18:37,100 --> 00:18:38,100
Coach!

292
00:18:39,133 --> 00:18:40,167
Coach, wake up!

293
00:18:41,500 --> 00:18:42,933
- Wake up!
- Coach!

294
00:18:43,000 --> 00:18:44,433
Wake up, Coach!

295
00:18:46,033 --> 00:18:49,433
Don't leave me, Coach!

296
00:18:49,500 --> 00:18:51,433
- Yen, that's enough.
- Coach!

297
00:18:51,500 --> 00:18:52,467
Yen, stop.

298
00:18:53,533 --> 00:18:54,667
Coach, wake up!

299
00:18:54,733 --> 00:18:55,867
Yen, that's enough!

300
00:18:55,967 --> 00:18:57,367
Coach!

301
00:19:00,567 --> 00:19:01,700
Wake up!

302
00:19:04,400 --> 00:19:05,333
Coach!

303
00:19:05,400 --> 00:19:06,700
Yen.

304
00:19:06,767 --> 00:19:07,800
Coach!

305
00:19:07,867 --> 00:19:09,100
Yen, that's enough!

306
00:19:09,600 --> 00:19:12,967
Amanda, I prepared
your favorite food.

307
00:19:13,033 --> 00:19:14,600
I'm sure you missed it.

308
00:19:15,767 --> 00:19:17,167
Let's go.

309
00:19:17,233 --> 00:19:18,933
I don't want to go home yet.

310
00:19:20,500 --> 00:19:22,200
Why?

311
00:19:22,267 --> 00:19:23,833
I want you to bring me
to someone

312
00:19:23,900 --> 00:19:29,733
who can give me an update
about the search.

313
00:19:32,900 --> 00:19:34,167
Okay.

314
00:19:34,233 --> 00:19:35,200
Let's go.

315
00:19:49,533 --> 00:19:52,900
It's a good thing that
you're aware of your mistakes.

316
00:19:52,967 --> 00:19:54,467
Now, learn from it.

317
00:19:54,533 --> 00:19:58,233
That's the difference
between winners and losers.

318
00:19:58,300 --> 00:20:01,267
Losers cry their hearts out.

319
00:20:01,333 --> 00:20:03,767
They drown themselves
in frustrations.

320
00:20:03,867 --> 00:20:06,933
But winners know
how to get up...

321
00:20:07,000 --> 00:20:08,600
and fight.

322
00:20:29,800 --> 00:20:31,267
Why is this happening?

323
00:20:35,767 --> 00:20:38,033
Why do I keep losing
the people I love?

324
00:20:44,033 --> 00:20:45,300
When I was ten,

325
00:20:48,233 --> 00:20:49,767
my mom was taken away from me.

326
00:20:52,033 --> 00:20:53,100
And now,

327
00:20:55,167 --> 00:20:57,267
my second mom...

328
00:21:01,300 --> 00:21:02,267
is gone too.

329
00:21:14,700 --> 00:21:16,600
Do you think we can get out
of this island?

330
00:21:21,033 --> 00:21:23,433
We might die here too.

331
00:21:26,833 --> 00:21:28,467
Don't think like that.

332
00:21:28,533 --> 00:21:30,400
Why not?

333
00:21:32,867 --> 00:21:35,433
Do you still think
someone will rescue us?

334
00:21:38,967 --> 00:21:42,967
You keep telling me
that someone will rescue us.

335
00:21:43,067 --> 00:21:44,367
But where are they?

336
00:21:46,767 --> 00:21:48,833
We've been here for days!

337
00:21:51,600 --> 00:21:54,333
And no one came to rescue us.

338
00:21:55,500 --> 00:21:57,433
And if they will rescue us,
why...

339
00:21:57,500 --> 00:22:00,900
wht not when my coach
needed help?

340
00:22:07,433 --> 00:22:08,400
Red...

341
00:22:09,800 --> 00:22:11,733
The world has forgotten
about us.

342
00:22:14,800 --> 00:22:15,833
It's over.

343
00:22:15,900 --> 00:22:18,267
We're going to die here.

344
00:22:18,333 --> 00:22:19,300
We're going to die.

345
00:22:19,367 --> 00:22:20,333
No!

346
00:22:21,667 --> 00:22:22,733
No, we're not going to die.

347
00:22:24,033 --> 00:22:25,333
I can't accept that!

348
00:22:26,433 --> 00:22:29,733
Can't you see what's going on?

349
00:22:31,567 --> 00:22:33,767
We have no hope!

350
00:22:34,867 --> 00:22:37,167
We're helpless!

351
00:22:37,233 --> 00:22:38,567
Maybe you're right!

352
00:22:38,633 --> 00:22:40,000
Maybe we have a little chance
of survival.

353
00:22:41,767 --> 00:22:45,633
But I won't give up no matter
how small our chances are.

354
00:22:46,867 --> 00:22:47,900
I will keep fighting.

355
00:22:49,367 --> 00:22:51,433
And we'll get out of this island
alive.

356
00:22:53,500 --> 00:22:55,067
I will do everything I can.

357
00:23:04,233 --> 00:23:07,367
Hopelessness is our enemy.

358
00:23:11,267 --> 00:23:12,600
And we can't let that defeat us.

359
00:23:14,200 --> 00:23:18,400
Think about someone
who's waiting for us.

360
00:23:19,433 --> 00:23:20,400
Think about your mom.

361
00:23:22,233 --> 00:23:23,433
My family.

362
00:23:29,000 --> 00:23:31,167
I promise
that we'll make it home.

363
00:23:34,333 --> 00:23:36,300
We can all celebrate together.

364
00:23:48,700 --> 00:23:51,533
This is all Amanda's fault!

365
00:23:51,600 --> 00:23:53,267
She ruined our family!

366
00:23:53,333 --> 00:23:57,200
And I will never, ever,
forgive her!

367
00:23:57,300 --> 00:24:01,633
You said you'd give me a call
for an update!

368
00:24:01,700 --> 00:24:05,467
I've been instructed
to tell the passengers' families

369
00:24:05,533 --> 00:24:07,833
that the longer
the search takes,

370
00:24:07,900 --> 00:24:11,667
the smaller the chance
of finding them alive.

371
00:24:11,733 --> 00:24:12,267
What?

372
00:24:12,333 --> 00:24:14,067
If we get this done

373
00:24:14,133 --> 00:24:15,733
and get to sail out,

374
00:24:15,800 --> 00:24:17,700
what do you think
we'll see first?

375
00:24:19,067 --> 00:24:20,067
A ship!

376
00:24:23,167 --> 00:24:24,800
Help!

377
00:24:24,867 --> 00:24:26,467
- Help!
- We're here!

378
00:24:26,533 --> 00:24:27,500
Help!

379
00:24:29,600 --> 00:24:31,167
- Help!
- We're here!
